.::Release Notes::.
-------------------
A lot of the tracks are named 'flow', because they are just freestyles without track names, not unlabeled tracks. As I told the person that requested this, the only original Greatest Hits released are the flow tracks, mixed by OG Ron C(Chopped & Screwed).

If you find yourself wishing you could hear the discs in a regular pitch, you can do a couple of things: 1. Have a stereo like mine where there's a pitch control, or 2. Download a free recording program off the internet, like Audacity, upload the tracks and change the pitch and speed yourself (I know that for Audacity you need to first convert the cd tracks, so you might also download something like db poweramp, also forever free.)Of course, you can also just forget the hassle of all this and just enjoy the songs as they are.
